{"title_page": "Carlton Anderson", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Carlton Anderson\n| image            = \n| image_upright    = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = \n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1992|7|1}}\n| birth_place      = [[Cypress, Texas|Cypress]], Texas, U.S.\n| origin           = \n| genre            = [[Country music|Country]]\n| occupation       = Singer, songwriter\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| years_active     = \n| label            = \n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = {{URL|http://carltonandersonmusic.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Carlton Anderson''' (born July 1, 1992) is an American [[country music]] singer-songwriter, based in [[Nashville, Tennessee]], United States.\n\n== Career ==\nAnderson grew up in [[Cypress, Texas]], before attending Belmont University and playing on [[Music City]]'s Lower Broadway.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/176820/sony-music-nashville-signs-carlton-anderson-to-ari|title=Sony Music Nashville Signs Carlton Anderson To Arista Imprint|website=Allaccess.com|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref> As a kid he worked odd jobs at the grocery store and oil fields to earn money to buy a guitar and PA.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://musicrow.com/2018/05/arista-nashville-signs-carlton-anderson/|title=Arista Nashville Signs Carlton Anderson|date=18 May 2018|website=Musicrow.com}}</ref> Anderson\u2019s musical influences begin with [[Willie Nelson]], who he refers to as \"his drug\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.megacountry.com/news/15051-new-artist-spotlight-carlton-anderson-766|title=New Artist Spotlight: Carlton Anderson |website=MegaCountry.com|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref> as well as [[George Strait]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tasteofcountry.com/carlton-anderson-drop-everything/|title=Is Carlton Anderson's 'Drop Everything' a Hit? Listen!|website=Taste of Country|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref>\n\nHis 1990s influenced sound has brought him recognition with a new crop of country artists including [[Riley Green (singer)|Riley Green]] and [[Cody Johnson]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/country/8464983/country-roots-showing-new-releases-embrace-old-school-sounds|title=Country's Roots Are Showing as New Releases Embrace Old-School Sounds|website=Billboard}}</ref> who Anderson has toured with in Nashville.  He released a self titled EP in 2014 with the songs \"Airplane\" and \"Forever\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.texaslocallive.com/single-post/2017/11/28/All-About-That-Bass-Carlton-Anderson|title=All About That Bass: Carlton Anderson {{!}} Tuning Texas {{!}} Monday Night Music Showcase|website=Tuning Texas {{!}} Monday Night Music Showcase|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref>\n\nHe signed with Sony Nashville in 2018 and released a debut single on May 18 called \"Drop Everything\". The track was co-written by [[Rhett Akins]], [[Matt Dragstrem]], and [[Ashley Gorley]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.radio.com/blogs/lauren-hoffman/listen-carlton-anderson-releases-debut-single-drop-everything|title=LISTEN: Carlton Anderson Releases Debut Single, \"Drop Everything\"|date=2018-05-29|website=Radio.com |access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thecountrynote.com/in-the-news/newly-signed-arista-nashville-artist-carlton-anderson-releases-debut-single-drop-everything/|title=Newly Signed Arista Nashville Artist Carlton Anderson Releases Debut Single, \"Drop Everything\"|date=25 May 2018|website=Thecountrynote.com}}</ref>\n\nHe was named the Breakthrough Artist of the Week on 979KickFM on May 25.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://979kickfm.com/breakthrough-artist-of-the-week-carlton-anderson/|title=Breakthrough Artist of the Week: Carlton Anderson|website=97.9 KICK FM|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref> Anderson parted ways with [[Arista Nashville]] in September 2019.\n\n==Discography==\n===Extended plays===\n*\u201dCarlton Anderson\u201d (Arista Nashville; 2019)\n\n===Singles===\n*\"Drop Everything\" (Sony Music Nashville; May 25, 2018)\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\u201cwikitable\u201d\n|-\n! Year\n! Video\n! Director\n|-\n| 2018\n| \u201cDrop Everything\u201d\n| Jeffrey C. Phillips\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://carltonandersonmusic.com/}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Anderson, Carlton}}\n[[Category:American country singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Arista Records artists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Harris County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Country musicians from Texas]]\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Carlton Anderson\n| image            = \n| image_upright    = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = \n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1992|7|1}}\n| birth_place      = [[Cypress, Texas|Cypress]], Texas, U.S.\n| origin           = \n| genre            = [[Country music|Country]]\n| occupation       = Singer, songwriter\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| years_active     = \n| label            = \n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = {{URL|http://carltonandersonmusic.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Carlton Anderson''' (born July 1, 1992) is an American [[country music]] singer-songwriter, based in [[Nashville, Tennessee]], United States.\n\n== Career ==\nAnderson grew up in [[Cypress, Texas]], before attending Belmont University and playing on [[Music City]]'s Lower Broadway.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/176820/sony-music-nashville-signs-carlton-anderson-to-ari|title=Sony Music Nashville Signs Carlton Anderson To Arista Imprint|website=Allaccess.com|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref> As a kid he worked odd jobs at the grocery store and oil fields to earn money to buy a guitar and PA.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://musicrow.com/2018/05/arista-nashville-signs-carlton-anderson/|title=Arista Nashville Signs Carlton Anderson|date=18 May 2018|website=Musicrow.com}}</ref> Anderson\u2019s musical influences begin with [[Willie Nelson]], who he refers to as \"his drug\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.megacountry.com/news/15051-new-artist-spotlight-carlton-anderson-766|title=New Artist Spotlight: Carlton Anderson |website=MegaCountry.com|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref> as well as [[George Strait]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tasteofcountry.com/carlton-anderson-drop-everything/|title=Is Carlton Anderson's 'Drop Everything' a Hit? Listen!|website=Taste of Country|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref>\n\nHis 1990s influenced sound has brought him recognition with a new crop of country artists including [[Riley Green (singer)|Riley Green]] and [[Cody Johnson]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/country/8464983/country-roots-showing-new-releases-embrace-old-school-sounds|title=Country's Roots Are Showing as New Releases Embrace Old-School Sounds|website=Billboard}}</ref> who Anderson has toured with in Nashville.  He released a self titled EP in 2014 with the songs \"Airplane\" and \"Forever\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.texaslocallive.com/single-post/2017/11/28/All-About-That-Bass-Carlton-Anderson|title=All About That Bass: Carlton Anderson {{!}} Tuning Texas {{!}} Monday Night Music Showcase|website=Tuning Texas {{!}} Monday Night Music Showcase|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref>\n\nHe signed with Sony Nashville in 2018 and released a debut single on May 18 called \"Drop Everything\". The track was co-written by [[Rhett Akins]], [[Matt Dragstrem]], and [[Ashley Gorley]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.radio.com/blogs/lauren-hoffman/listen-carlton-anderson-releases-debut-single-drop-everything|title=LISTEN: Carlton Anderson Releases Debut Single, \"Drop Everything\"|date=2018-05-29|website=Radio.com |access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thecountrynote.com/in-the-news/newly-signed-arista-nashville-artist-carlton-anderson-releases-debut-single-drop-everything/|title=Newly Signed Arista Nashville Artist Carlton Anderson Releases Debut Single, \u201cDrop Everything\u201d|date=25 May 2018|website=Thecountrynote.com}}</ref>\n\nHe was named the Breakthrough Artist of the Week on 979KickFM on May 25.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://979kickfm.com/breakthrough-artist-of-the-week-carlton-anderson/|title=Breakthrough Artist of the Week: Carlton Anderson|website=97.9 KICK FM|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref> Anderson parted ways with [[Arista Nashville]] in September 2019.\n\n==Discography==\n===Extended plays===\n*\u201dCarlton Anderson\u201d (Arista Nashville; 2019)\n\n===Singles===\n*\"Drop Everything\" (Sony Music Nashville; May 25, 2018)\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\u201cwikitable\u201d\n|-\n! Year\n! Video\n! Director\n|-\n| 2018\n| \u201cDrop Everything\u201d\n| Jeffrey C. Phillips\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://carltonandersonmusic.com/}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Anderson, Carlton}}\n[[Category:American country singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Arista Records artists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Harris County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Country musicians from Texas]]\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlton_Anderson"}
